name: sqsgenerator

new_version_errors.0.0.4:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '0.0.4' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://github.com/dnoeger/<{name}}/archive/<{version}}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "sqsgenerator" %}
{% set version = "0.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/dgehringer/{{ name }}/archive/refs/tags/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 983e20a97203b37dc4d21850e1a9693023cb1516bf543f645cbbac198a84f23c
  patches:
    - fixes.patch

build:
  number: 4
  entry_points:
    - sqsgen = sqsgenerator.cli:cli
  script_env:
    - CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS=-O2 -DNDEBUG  # [not win]
    - CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS=/O2 /DNDEBUG /MD /Zc:twoPhase- /DBOOST_PYTHON_STATIC_LIB /DBOOST_NUMPY_STATIC_LIB  # [win and py<=38]
    - CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS=/O2 /DNDEBUG /MD /Zc:twoPhase- /DBOOST_PYTHON_STATIC_LIB /DBOOST_NUMPY_STATIC_LIB /DHAVE_SNPRINTF  # [win and py>=39]
    - SQS_CMAKE_VERBOSE_MAKEFILE=ON  # [win]
    - SQS_FORWARD_WHITELIST=CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH  # [win]
    - SQS_CMAKE_MSVC_RUNTIME_LIBRARY=MultiThreadedDLL  # [win]
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  skip: true  # [py<35]

requirements:
  build:
    - pip
    - six
    - make           # [unix]
    - cmake >=3.12.0
    - ninja          # [win]
    - numpy
    - python
    - boost
    - boost-cpp
    - llvm-openmp    # [osx]
    - libgomp        # [linux]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - pip
    - six
    - ninja  # [win]
    - numpy
    - python
    - boost
    - boost-cpp
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - libgomp      # [linux]
  run:
    - pip
    - six
    - rich
    - numpy
    - click
    - python
    - pyyaml
    - frozendict
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - libgomp      # [linux]
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - {{ pin_compatible('boost') }}
    - {{ pin_compatible('boost-cpp') }}

test:
  imports:
    - sqsgenerator
  commands:
    - pip check

about:
  home: https://github.com/dgehringer/sqsgenerator
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: A command line tool written in Python/C++ to analyse short-range order or generate SQS structures

  description: |
    This package is a Special Quasirandom Structure generator written 
    in Python3/C++
  doc_url: https://sqsgenerator.readthedocs.io/en/latest
  dev_url: https://github.com/dgehringer/sqsgenerator

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jan-janssen
    - dgehringer
